and you can use them.

01:07:58.000 --> 01:08:01.000
The last part is the feedback.

01:08:02.000 --> 01:08:05.000
If we go back a few steps

01:08:05.000 --> 01:08:08.000
to the beginning of the course

01:08:08.000 --> 01:08:11.000
when we talked about insufficient and excessive leadership

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:14.000
I noticed that your attention was focused

01:08:14.000 --> 01:08:17.000
on the fact that you need to communicate with your subordinates

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:20.000
constantly.

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:23.000
The problem is that we don't always know

01:08:23.000 --> 01:08:26.000
how to give the right feedback.

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:29.000
We have a mentality of communication

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:33.000
of the post-Soviet space.

01:08:33.000 --> 01:08:36.000
When a person or a subordinate makes a mistake

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:39.000
or acts in the wrong direction

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:42.000
we usually express our indignation and comments to him.

01:08:42.000 --> 01:08:45.000
He or she listens carefully

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:48.000
and says that he or she will not repeat this mistake again.

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:51.000
I consider it a mistake

01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:54.000
and he or she may not consider it a mistake

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:57.000
because he or she tried.

01:08:58.000 --> 01:09:01.000
The probability of a mistake is high.

01:09:01.000 --> 01:09:04.000
A person will feel emotional tension

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:07.000
and emotional fear

01:09:07.000 --> 01:09:10.000
because he or she is afraid

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:13.000
to make the next mistake

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:16.000
because you will call him or her again

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:19.000
and report to him or her.

01:09:19.000 --> 01:09:22.000
There are more modern methods of feedback

01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:25.000
when communication is not about me talking to you

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:28.000
but about the interaction of two sides.

01:09:28.000 --> 01:09:31.000
The feedback is not about me expressing my comments.

01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:34.000
The feedback is about your opinion

01:09:34.000 --> 01:09:37.000
and how we can fix it together

01:09:37.000 --> 01:09:40.000
in order not to repeat the mistake.

01:09:40.000 --> 01:09:43.000
In order to effectively give feedback

01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:46.000
and interact with subordinates

01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:49.000
in the process of group dynamics

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:52.000
when people are at different stages

01:09:52.000 --> 01:09:55.000
of change curve

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:58.000
when people feel stress

01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:01.000
when they make mistakes

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:04.000
there are three basic rules.

01:10:04.000 --> 01:10:07.000
You can see them on the slide.

01:10:07.000 --> 01:10:10.000
The first one is to give the employee

01:10:10.000 --> 01:10:13.000
an opportunity to realize his or her behavior.

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:16.000
In other words

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:19.000
I call my subordinate

01:10:19.000 --> 01:10:22.000
Fedya Ivanov

01:10:22.000 --> 01:10:25.000
who is three days late

01:10:25.000 --> 01:10:28.000
in order to avoid

01:10:28.000 --> 01:10:31.000
repeating the mistake.

01:10:31.000 --> 01:10:34.000
A person who feels emotional tension

01:10:34.000 --> 01:10:37.000
will continue to be late.

01:10:37.000 --> 01:10:40.000
There is another type of feedback.

01:10:40.000 --> 01:10:43.000
I report that for three days

01:10:43.000 --> 01:10:46.000
I don't see you at your workplace.

01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:49.000
You are late.

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:52.000
I want to understand what is going on.

01:10:52.000 --> 01:10:55.000
Tell me about it.

01:10:55.000 --> 01:10:58.000
You need to give the person an opportunity

01:10:58.000 --> 01:11:01.000
to tell what is going on.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:04.000
The subordinate tells you

01:11:04.000 --> 01:11:07.000
that he takes his child to kindergarten in the morning.

01:11:07.000 --> 01:11:10.000
He can't bring it earlier

01:11:10.000 --> 01:11:13.000
because the kindergarten is still closed.

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:16.000
He is late for work.

01:11:16.000 --> 01:11:19.000
The next step is

01:11:19.000 --> 01:11:22.000
to analyze the consequences of his behavior

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:25.000
together with the subordinate.

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:28.000
How critical they are

01:11:28.000 --> 01:11:31.000
to the business processes of my unit.

01:11:31.000 --> 01:11:34.000
If they are very critical

01:11:34.000 --> 01:11:37.000
and we analyze it together with the subordinate

01:11:37.000 --> 01:11:40.000
we move to the third step

01:11:40.000 --> 01:11:43.000
and agree on the consequences.

01:11:43.000 --> 01:11:46.000
The second step is

01:11:46.000 --> 01:11:49.000
to show the consequences of the behavior.

01:11:49.000 --> 01:11:52.000
In our case, the subordinate is late three times in a row.

01:11:52.000 --> 01:11:55.000
I think that in my unit

01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:58.000
it critically affects the business processes

01:11:58.000 --> 01:12:01.000
because I have clear formal procedures.

01:12:01.000 --> 01:12:04.000
No employee is ever late

01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:07.000
because everyone is fined for being late.

01:12:07.000 --> 01:12:10.000
I have a right to fire an employee

01:12:10.000 --> 01:12:13.000
after three official notes.

01:12:13.000 --> 01:12:16.000
It is critical for the person

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:19.000
and for the business processes

01:12:19.000 --> 01:12:22.000
because I lose a specialist.

01:12:22.000 --> 01:12:25.000
I explain the consequences

01:12:25.000 --> 01:12:28.000
of his behavior.

01:12:28.000 --> 01:12:31.000
We move to the third step

01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:34.000
when we agree on how we will act.

01:12:35.000 --> 01:12:38.000
I allow him to come to work at 10 am

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:41.000
and he will leave at 7 pm.

01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:44.000
Or we look for other opportunities

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:47.000
and compromises.

01:12:47.000 --> 01:12:50.000
Remember that considering the roles in the team

01:12:50.000 --> 01:12:53.000
everyone perceives the opposite critical relationship

01:12:53.000 --> 01:12:56.000
in a different way.

01:12:56.000 --> 01:12:59.000
It is important to remember it.

01:12:59.000 --> 01:13:02.000
We will talk about personalities

01:13:03.000 --> 01:13:06.000
and psychological states.

01:13:06.000 --> 01:13:09.000
This course will help you to understand

01:13:09.000 --> 01:13:12.000
each person's psychological state.

01:13:12.000 --> 01:13:15.000
However, if we focus on the roles in the team

01:13:15.000 --> 01:13:18.000
there are four doses of feedback.

01:13:18.000 --> 01:13:21.000
The first dose is a glass.

01:13:21.000 --> 01:13:24.000
People who perceive feedback critically

01:13:24.000 --> 01:13:27.000
are not ready to perceive it in large pieces

01:13:27.000 --> 01:13:30.000
because they close their eyes

01:13:31.000 --> 01:13:34.000
and they worry about it.

01:13:34.000 --> 01:13:37.000
They lose self-esteem.

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:40.000
The next dose is a type of people

01:13:40.000 --> 01:13:43.000
who can catch not more than three points

01:13:43.000 --> 01:13:46.000
of critical comments.

01:13:46.000 --> 01:13:49.000
The previous one was just a little.

01:13:49.000 --> 01:13:52.000
This type of people has not more than three points

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:55.000
of feedback.

01:13:55.000 --> 01:13:58.000
These three points should be related

01:13:59.000 --> 01:14:02.000
to each topic or three points to one topic.

01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:05.000
There are variations.

01:14:05.000 --> 01:14:08.000
However, you should not give more than three critical comments

01:14:08.000 --> 01:14:11.000
to a person in a glass.

01:14:11.000 --> 01:14:14.000
The consequences will be the same.

01:14:14.000 --> 01:14:17.000
A person will close himself

01:14:17.000 --> 01:14:20.000
and feel a strong internal pressure.

01:14:20.000 --> 01:14:23.000
He will not have a trust relationship with you.

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:26.000
This is important in the team.

01:14:27.000 --> 01:14:30.000
The next dose is a barrel.

01:14:30.000 --> 01:14:33.000
People who can perceive feedback

01:14:33.000 --> 01:14:36.000
are people with adequate self-esteem

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:39.000
who want to develop

01:14:39.000 --> 01:14:42.000
and even demand it.

01:14:42.000 --> 01:14:45.000
They say they want to improve

01:14:45.000 --> 01:14:48.000
and they want to know everything.

01:14:48.000 --> 01:14:51.000
When you give them a large amount of feedback

01:14:51.000 --> 01:14:54.000
it does not strain them

01:14:54.000 --> 01:14:57.000
because feedback helps them to develop.

01:14:57.000 --> 01:15:00.000
It is believed that this category of employees

01:15:00.000 --> 01:15:03.000
who get a barrel dose

01:15:03.000 --> 01:15:06.000
with adequate self-esteem

01:15:06.000 --> 01:15:09.000
and the most progressive category of employees

01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:12.000
is the easiest to develop.

01:15:12.000 --> 01:15:15.000
The last dose is a barrel.

01:15:15.000 --> 01:15:18.000
These are employees who can get a large amount of feedback

01:15:18.000 --> 01:15:21.000
and a crazy amount of feedback.

01:15:21.000 --> 01:15:24.000
They can say anything they want

01:15:24.000 --> 01:15:27.000
and do anything they want.

01:15:27.000 --> 01:15:30.000
You probably have such a category of employees.

01:15:30.000 --> 01:15:33.000
They will listen to you carefully

01:15:33.000 --> 01:15:36.000
and will not be offended.

01:15:36.000 --> 01:15:39.000
They will agree with you

01:15:39.000 --> 01:15:42.000
and will not even try to correct their behavior.

01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:45.000
We say in Russian that it is like peas in a pod.

01:15:45.000 --> 01:15:48.000
You say what you want

01:15:48.000 --> 01:15:51.000
and you will not be offended.

01:15:51.000 --> 01:15:54.000
You will not even try to blame the person

01:15:54.000 --> 01:15:57.000
for doing something wrong.

01:15:57.000 --> 01:16:00.000
He will take everything as a peasant's barrel

01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:03.000
and it will be impossible to observe

01:16:03.000 --> 01:16:06.000
the result of his work and changes.

01:16:06.000 --> 01:16:09.000
To give the right feedback to the right people

01:16:09.000 --> 01:16:12.000
you should get acquainted with this topic

01:16:12.000 --> 01:16:15.000
in the personality and psychological block.

